    <!-- About Section Start -->
    <section class="section" id="about" style="padding: 100px 0;">
        <div class="container-fluid px-3 px-md-4 px-xxl-5">
            <div class="row justify-content-center">
                <div class="col-12">
                    <div class="about-content">
                        <div class="row align-items-center">
                            <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-5 mb-4 mb-md-0">
                                <img src="images/picture2.png" class="img-fluid rounded-3" alt="Chaitanya Krishna">
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-lg-8 col-md-7">
                                <h4 class="mb-3" style="font-size: 1.75rem;">About Me</h4>
                                <p class="text-muted mb-3" style="line-height: 1.8;">
                                    Over the last 10+ years, I’ve worked across consulting and enterprise environments, including engagements with both government and private organisations. I began my career doing hands-on security assessments, including vulnerability assessments, penetration testing, and security reviews, before moving into threat intelligence and security operations. I realised early on that finding problems is only half the job; fixing them in a repeatable, operational way is where the real value lies.
                                </p>
                                <p class="text-muted mb-3" style="line-height: 1.8;">
                                    My core strength is taking messy, unclear security problems and turning them into practical outcomes: cleaner detections, faster response, and less unnecessary noise for security teams. I spend a lot of time working with OSINT and security automation, and I enjoy building small, focused tools including GenAI assisted workflows that help teams move faster without compromising on fundamentals.
                                </p>
                                <p class="text-muted mb-4" style="line-height: 1.8;">
                                    I also write and mentor alongside my work. Not for visibility, but to document what actually works, highlight common mistakes, and share lessons that teams usually learn the hard way.
                                </p>

                                <div class="mt-4">
                                    <h5 class="mb-3" style="font-size: 1.15rem; font-weight: 700;">My Philosophy</h5>
                                    <ul class="text-muted" style="line-height: 1.8; padding-left: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 0;">
                                        <li class="mb-2"><strong>Clarity over noise:</strong> The goal isn’t more alerts it's fewer surprises. I aim for detections and processes that are simple to understand and easy to operate.</li>
                                        <li class="mb-2"><strong>Automate the repeatable:</strong> If a task happens more than a few times, it deserves automation. Human time should go to judgment, investigation, and learning.</li>
                                        <li class="mb-2"><strong>Trust, but verify:</strong> OSINT and telemetry are inputs not truth. I validate signals, corroborate sources, and document assumptions before escalating.</li>
                                        <li class="mb-2"><strong>Build with empathy:</strong> Security should enable teams, not block them. I try to meet people where they are and make secure paths the easiest paths.</li>
                                    </ul>
                                </div>
                                
                                <!-- Skills -->
                                <div class="mt-4">
                                    <span class="skill-tag">Cloud Security</span>
                                    <span class="skill-tag">Threat Intelligence</span>
                                    <span class="skill-tag">Incident Response</span>
                                    <span class="skill-tag">Security Automation</span>
                                    <span class="skill-tag">OSINT</span>
                                    <span class="skill-tag">GenAI</span>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    <!-- About Section End -->

